        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 10:23PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1023 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
southeast of Chetopa, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Picher...                         Cardin...
Peoria...                         Commerce...
Welch...                          Quapaw...
Miami...                          Treece...
Baxter Springs...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 308 and 324.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
